videos.description: Anthony Brown throws into double coverage and gets intercepted by Shawn Boone after the ball is tipped.
videos.headline: NC State's Boone gets the tip drill INT

videos.description: NC State attempts a flea flicker but it goes wrong when Ryan Finley is sacked by Boston College's  Ray Smith.
videos.headline: BC stops NC State's flea flicker

videos.description: After a flea flicker, Boston College picks up a first down on an 18-yard pass from Anthony Brown to Travis Levy.
videos.headline: BC converts on flea flicker

videos.description: AJ Dillon goes untouched on a 66-yard touchdown run that gives Boston College a 7-0 lead.
videos.headline: BC's Dillon breaks off 66-yard TD

videos.description: Jaylen Samuels finishes his 8-yard touchdown run by reaching the ball over the pylon.
videos.headline: NC State's Samuels reaches over pylon for TD

videos.description: Ryan Finley's screen pass is intercepted by Boston College linebacker Ty Schwab.
videos.headline: Schwab makes diving INT

videos.description: Boston College head coach Steve Addazio says that they need to stick to the game plan and clean up their mistakes in the second half against NC State.
videos.headline: Addazio says Boston College will stick to game plan in 2nd half

videos.description: Bradley Chubb passes Mario Williams for most sacks by an NC State player with his sack of Darius Wade.
videos.headline: Chubb becomes NC State's sack leader

videos.description: Jaylen Samuels throws a lateral pass that isn't caught and is recovered by Boston College's Kevin Bletzer.
videos.headline: Bletzer recovers NC State's lateral

videos.description: Thadd Smith dives into the end zone for a Boston College touchdown that gives the Eagles the lead.
videos.headline: Smith dives for TD

videos.description: Nyheim Hines takes the handoff 50 yards to the house and gives NC State a 17-14 lead.
videos.headline: Wolfpack's Hines goes for 50-yard TD

videos.description: After their 17-14 win at Boston College, NC State head coach Dave Doeren likes his teams chances at going 7-1 in conference for the first time.
videos.headline: Doeren likes where his team is at moving forward
